        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 2:18PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 218 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harvest, or 8 miles north of Madison, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Huntsville, Madison, Athens, Moores Mill, Meridianville,
Alabama A And M University, Harvest, Huntsville International
Airport, French Mill, and Toney.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
